tp_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/19199-pryme8/?do_eq_hovercard_qt_ data-mentionid_eq__qt_19199_qt_ href_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/19199-pryme8/_qt_ rel_eq__qt__qt__gt_@Pryme8_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_blockquote class_eq__qt_ipsQuote_qt_ data-ipsquote_eq__qt__qt_ data-ipsquote-contentapp_eq__qt_forums_qt_ data-ipsquote-contentclass_eq__qt_forums_Topic_qt_ data-ipsquote-contentcommentid_eq__qt_139635_qt_ data-ipsquote-contentid_eq__qt_24173_qt_ data-ipsquote-contenttype_eq__qt_forums_qt_ data-ipsquote-timestamp_eq__qt_1470953437_qt_ data-ipsquote-userid_eq__qt_19199_qt_ data-ipsquote-username_eq__qt_Pryme8_qt__gt_\n\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsQuote_citation_qt__gt_\n\t\tOn 8/12/2016 at 1_dd_10 AM_co_ Pryme8 said_dd_\n\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsQuote_contents_qt__gt_\n\t\t_lt_p_gt_\n\t\t\tUm_co_ I can maybe make something for you... It will be a custom shader.\n\t\t_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_p_gt_\n\t\t\tIs there a need for transparency?\n\t\t_lt_/p_gt_\n\t_lt_/div_gt_\n_lt_/blockquote_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tTransparency would be nice. How would the shader you intend to write be different from the PG _lt_a contenteditable_eq__qt_false_qt_ data-ipshover_eq__qt__qt_ data-ipshover-target_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/5733-wingnut/?do_eq_hovercard_qt_ data-mentionid_eq__qt_5733_qt_ href_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/5733-wingnut/_qt_ rel_eq__qt__qt__gt_@Wingnut_lt_/a_gt_ linked to?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Pryme8","Date":"2016-08-16T14:34:29Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t_lt_p_gt_\n\tIts not I just noticed it_co_ you should go with that solution_co_ I have not had time to look at a sprite shader yet.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"royibernthal","Date":"2016-08-16T23:18:31Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t_lt_p_gt_\n\tI see. Any idea about my follow-up questions?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2016-08-17T02:23:44Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tHi Roy/P8.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t1 &amp_sm_ 2.  Dunno.  I_t_m not a shaderbuilder pilot.  But I have another idea. More about that_co_ soon. _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_a contenteditable_eq__qt_false_qt_ data-ipshover_eq__qt__qt_ data-ipshover-target_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/13038-nasimiasl/?do_eq_hovercard_qt_ data-mentionid_eq__qt_13038_qt_ href_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/profile/13038-nasimiasl/_qt_ rel_eq__qt__qt__gt_@NasimiAsl_lt_/a_gt_ is the author (and darned good driver) of shaderbuilder.  I have now pinged him_co_ so he might answer your typescript-&gt_sm_shaderbuilder questions_co_ maybe.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  I_t_m also not a typescript user.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_o_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_ohmy.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/ohmy@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_o_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tOk_co_ thinking about _lt_a href_eq__qt_http_dd_//babylonjs-playground.azurewebsites.net/#2GYRPB%231_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_this playground_lt_/a_gt_ again... we all know that I am sliding the spritemap sideways_co_ each frame_co_ a certain amount... to cause the animation.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBut there_t_s another way.  On each of the 4 corners of that box face... there are (or could be)... UVs.  They are vector2_t_s_co_ and they are likely_co_ currently_co_ set like this...\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tlower left - 0_co_0_lt_br /_gt_\n\tlower right - 1_co_0_lt_br /_gt_\n\tupper left - 0_co_1_lt_br /_gt_\n\tupper right - 1_co_1\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tYou can think of these as percentages... 0 means 0%_co_ 1 mean 100%.  These values are used to map textures to that face.  Those settings that I show... indicate the texture will be mapped 100% tall and 100% wide... across the 4 face UV_t_s.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo let_t_s pretend you had a real wide sprite map... like a film strip... 20 frames of sprites... side by side.  The texture is one sprite tall_co_ 20 sprites wide.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNow_co_ what if... you replaced those 4 UV_t_s on the box/button face... and made them be...\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tlower left - 0_co_0_lt_br /_gt_\n\tlower right - .05_co_0_lt_br /_gt_\n\tupper left - 0_co_1_lt_br /_gt_\n\tupper right - .1_co_1\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tThat would _t_map_t_ the first frame (of our 20-wide sprite film-strip)... across the entire face.  Can you see why?  Let_t_s move to the next frame...\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tlower left - .05_co_0_lt_br /_gt_\n\tlower right - .1_co_0_lt_br /_gt_\n\tupper left - .05_co_1_lt_br /_gt_\n\tupper right - .15_co_1\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tNow we_t_ve put the second frame... across the face.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSee the pattern?  The x values of our UVs... only increment a tiny bit per frame.  0%_co_ then 5%_co_ then 10%_co_ then 15%.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tInstead of moving the sprite map sideways with xOffset (like I did in that pg)_co_ do -&gt_sm_ replace 4 UV_t_s_co_ replace 4 UV_t_s_co_ replace 4 UV_t_s_co_ replace 4 UV_t_s_co_ etc etc.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIn a way_co_ you are turning the teeth of the gears that move the film strip ahead_co_ one frame at a time.  Click_co_ click_co_ etc.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI think I saw Raanan... divide-up a single videoTexture and place portions of it...  on many tiles of planes... using this _qt_tiny UV increments_qt_ thing.  Worked great. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI_t_m no pro_co_ not even close_co_ but UV-wrangling seems to be a Good Thing_lt_span style_eq__qt_font-size_dd_8px_sm__qt__gt_tm _lt_/span_gt__lt_span style_eq__qt_font-size_dd_14px_sm__qt__gt_to know about_co_ and to be an expert-of.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  I wish I was.  _lt_/span_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_span style_eq__qt_font-size_dd_14px_sm__qt__gt_I think this is yet another _lt_s_gt_good_lt_/s_gt_ way of animating on a face.  It is similar to my xOffset method_co_ but with zero positional drift.  In other words... if you make your sprite map accurately_co_ the sprite frames will get _lt_u_gt_tightly_lt_/u_gt_-locked to those UV_t_s and should look great._lt_/span_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t_lt_span style_eq__qt_font-size_dd_14px_sm__qt__gt_IF you master this... then yes!  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.p